Class JmsDestinationFactory

All Implemented Interfaces:
javax.naming.spi.ObjectFactory
public class JmsDestinationFactory
extends java.lang.Object
implements javax.naming.spi.ObjectFactory

This factory object implements the ObjectFactory interface and is used to resolve a reference to an administered destination. This is part of our JNDI support.

All JmsDestination objects support the java.naming.Referenceable interface and make explicit reference to this factory
